From a5f1c1ec85c569b9b6b1c48968f3ed280ba3f289 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mark Stapp <mjs@cisco.com>
Date: Wed, 20 Aug 2025 13:29:19 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] lib, build: support gperftools tcmalloc, release free memory
 to host OS

The tcmalloc library that's part of the gperftools project can be built
with an option to return free memory back to the host OS. That can help
avoid OOM situations.

This adds a configure option (--enable-gperf-tcmalloc) to use tcmalloc
once it's built. If enabled, a background timer runs in the daemons,
asking tcmalloc to return free memory periodically.

Also fixes memory display to support values >2GB in mtype_memstr().

Ported from FRRouting/frr#19377 (merged Oct 21, 2025)
Signed-off-by: Ravi Minnikanti <rminnikanti@marvell.com>
